<!--start left column-->
<div class="g8">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold;">For more information or to book this Explorer Holiday please call 01483 345 805</p>
<p>Enjoy the best of the beautiful region of Tuscany with this Explorer Holiday based in the spa town of Montecatini. Days out are included to visit the historic towns of Florence, Siena and San Gimignano and the wine-growing region of Chianti. Accompanied by your friendly Inghams Representative and with plenty of free time to relax, this is the perfect Tuscan holiday</p>
<p> </p>
<h2>HIGHLIGHTS</h2>
<ul>
<li>7 nights at the 4 star <a data-udi="umb://document/074ee7813ef64428b3982b31d9f31c38" href="/{localLink:umb://document/074ee7813ef64428b3982b31d9f31c38}" title="Treasures of Tuscany"><strong>Hotel Francia &amp; Quirinale</strong></a> with outdoor pool.</li>
<li>Half board included</li>
<li>Assistance throughout from an Inghams Representative.</li>
<li>Trip to nearby Florence including guided tour of the historical centre and Uffizi Gallery.</li>
<li>Day out to visit historic Siena and charming San Gimignano.</li>
<li>Discover the beautiful Chianti countryside and taste the local wine.</li>
<li>Join your Representative for optional days out to visit Lucca and Pisa by train.</li>
<li>Optional excursion to the Cinque Terre.</li>
<li>Plenty of time to relax and enjoy Montecatini and its spas.</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<h2>ITINERARY</h2>
<p><strong>Day 1 | </strong>Fly to Pisa from a selection of UK regional airports and transfer to your hotel in <strong>Montecatini</strong>. In the evening meet your fellow travellers and friendly Inghams Representative.</p>
<p><strong>Day 2 | </strong>Today we visit the beautiful region of <strong>Chianti</strong><strong>,</strong> known throughout the world for its superb wines and also for its unique landscape of rolling hills. We stop for wine tasting in one of the area’s wineries.</p>
<p><strong>Day 3 | </strong>Today we take the train to visit the incredible city of <strong>Florence</strong> with a guided tour of the world famous Uffizi Gallery and the Duomo.</p>
<p><strong>Day 4 | </strong>A day at leisure in Montecatini. Perhaps take the funicular up to the charming hilltop village of Montecatini Alto to admire the views or take a treatment at one of the resort's spas. There is also the chance to take an optional excursion to the <strong>Cinque Terre</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>Day 5 | </strong>A day trip to see the historic town of <strong>Siena</strong> and visit the beautiful Gothic cathedral. Then onwards to <strong>San Gimignano</strong>, famous for its many medieval towers.</p>
<p><strong>Day 6 | </strong>Another day at leisure with the chance to join your Representative for a trip to the pretty, walled town of <strong>Lucca</strong>. Not far away is <strong>Pisa</strong> and the famous leaning tower.</p>
<p><strong>Day 7 | </strong>A day to relax and enjoy the hotel’s pool or perhaps pick up some bargains in Montecatini’s great shops.</p>
<p><strong>Day 8 | </strong>Transfer provided to Pisa airport for your return flight to the UK. For those wishing to explore further why not create your own multi-centre holiday and add on a few days in another of our wonderful Italian destinations. </p>
</div>
